 As this service is listed on the Department of Education & Training Bushfire At-Risk Register, the approved provider must ensure that:

                       i.             to the Regulatory Authority through the National Quality Agenda Information Technology System (NQA ITS) public portal; and

ServiceName: Camp Australia - Boneo Primary School OSHC

Conditions on Approval:
This service approval, to the extent that it relates to an associated children’s service authorises the approved provider to operate a limited hours type 2 service within the meaning of regulation 5 of the Children’s Services Regulations 2009, and is subject to the following conditions:
1. The service approval is granted subject to the condition that the approved associated children’s service is operated in a way that—
(a) ensures the safety of the children being cared for or educated; and
(b) ensures that the developmental needs of those children are met; and
(c) supports the health and wellbeing of those children.
2. The service approval is granted subject to the condition that a person must not manage or control the operation of the approved associated children’s service in the absence of the approved provider unless the person is:
(a) the nominated supervisor for the education and care service (for the associated education and care service); or
(b) the holder of a supervisor certificate and is employed or engaged by the approved associated children’s service or the associated education and care service; or
(c) a person approved by the Secretary under section 25X of the Children’s Services Act 1996 (Vic).
3. The approved associated children’s service may care for or educate a maximum of 26 children. 
4. The number of school children cared for or educated by the approved associated children’s service must not exceed 30 per cent of the total number of places for the limited hours type 2. The number is 7.
5. Each child cannot be cared for or educated for more than 5 hours a day and not more than a total of 15 hours per week. 
6. The approved associated children’s service will operate from LH & OSHC Room one.
7. Except as otherwise provided, the requirements of the Act and the Regulations, must be met in relation to the limited hours type 2 service.
8. These conditions apply solely to the approved associated children’s service.

ServiceName: Bubup Womindjeka Family and Children's Centre
ProviderLegalName: Bubup Womindjeka Family & Children’s Centre Association Inc

Conditions on Approval:
This service approval, to the extent that it relates to an associated children’s service authorises the approved provider to operate a limited hours type 2 service within the meaning of regulation 5 of the Children’s Services Regulations 2009, and is subject to the following conditions:
1. The service approval is granted subject to the condition that the approved associated children’s service is operated in a way that—
(a) ensures the safety of the children being cared for or educated; and
(b) ensures that the developmental needs of those children are met; and
(c) supports the health and wellbeing of those children.
2. The service approval is granted subject to the condition that a person must not manage or control the operation of the approved associated children’s service in the absence of the approved provider unless the person is:
(a) the nominated supervisor for the education and care service (for the associated education and care service); or
(b) the holder of a supervisor certificate and is employed or engaged by the approved associated children’s service or the associated education and care service; or
(c) a person approved by the Secretary under section 25X of the Children’s Services Act 1996 (Vic).
3. The approved associated children’s service may care for or educate a maximum of 10 children. 
4. The number of school children cared for or educated by the approved associated children’s service must not exceed 30 per cent of the total number of places for the limited hours type 2. The number is 3.
5. Each child cannot be cared for or educated for more than 5 hours a day and not more than a total of 15 hours per week. 
6. The approved associated children’s service will operate play group room 1.
7. Except as otherwise provided, the requirements of the Act and the Regulations, must be met in relation to the limited hours type 2 service.
8. These conditions apply solely to the approved associated children’s service.
The Approved Provider must ensure the Regulatory Authority is advised within 14 days if the service waiver is no longer required.
